{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 12:16:12.765528", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission summary:\n- Anomaly detected: Yes\n- Faulty devices: controller\n- Root cause: southbound_port_block\n\nRationale:\n- All OVS switches have IP reachability to the controller host (20.0.0.100) but cannot establish the OpenFlow TCP session to 20.0.0.100:6633 (is_connected=false, last_error=\"Connection timed out\").\n- No OpenFlow flows present and fail_mode=secure, causing drop-all behavior and ARP failures.\n- Symptoms indicate the OpenFlow service port is not reachable despite host reachability, consistent with TCP/6633 being blocked by a firewall/ACL on the controller side (southbound port blocked).", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 1803, "output_tokens": 146, "total_tokens": 1949, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 1280}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
